trend_summary: Built-up cover steadily grows, led by northeastern urban sprawl, new arterial roads and a rapidly expanding quarryâ€“industrial complex in the south-east. Farmland is lost or fragmented, yet extensive fields and western forests remain, keeping overall form suburban with medium density.
notable_changes: Open-pit quarry in the south-east triples in size and gains adjacent spoil heaps and plants.
Residential neighbourhoods radiate from the northeastern city core, filling former fields.
A new ring/arterial road appears across the north, adding interchanges and widening later.
Several east-central fields convert to light-industrial or warehouse estates.
Western forest block stays stable, while scattered field plots nearby show gradual greening or reforestation.
